WEBVTT

00:00.160 --> 00:04.160
The development of feudalism eventually brought the flourishing of medieval cities.

00:05.280 --> 00:10.160
The main characteristic of the medieval cities was their placement within the fortress territory.

00:11.280 --> 00:15.040
The fortresses were used for defense purposes as well as for shelter.

00:16.080 --> 00:21.600
By the end of the 14th century, the Albanian territories were divided into three princedoms,

00:21.600 --> 00:27.120
Skutari, Daira, and Arta. The medieval culture was also well developed.

00:28.080 --> 00:33.760
This pavilion includes Albanian cities in the Middle Age, mural painting.

00:34.800 --> 00:40.080
Arms and coins used in the Middle Ages. Distribution of medieval princedoms.

00:41.120 --> 00:44.000
Archaeological objects of the 14th century.

